Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.18,0:00:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're so happy you\Ncould come have lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.66,0:00:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with your father\Nand me, Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.10,0:00:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.78,0:00:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was super awesome\Nof you to invite me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.28,0:00:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Things have been so busy\Nwith the Wonderbolts lately;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.78,0:00:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it's great to get a chance\Nto relax someplace quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.96,0:00:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly what I intend\Nto do now that I've retired.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.18,0:00:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I converted\Nthe back house
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.00,0:00:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to showcase my\Ncloud collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.44,0:00:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my clouds; your\Nmom has her flowers;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.42,0:00:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got your animals\Nand your brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.42,0:00:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr Breeze has\Nhis... interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.50,0:00:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say. Remember when he\Nwas convinced square clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.02,0:00:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,were gonna be the next\Nbig thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He's matured a\Nlot since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.48,0:00:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's funny\Nyou bring Zephyr up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.82,0:00:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! Not again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.16,0:00:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just for a\Nlittle while, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.84,0:00:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Till he gets back\Non his hooves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.40,0:01:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. You don't mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.70,0:01:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who's home?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.66,0:01:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, big sis,\Nit's your one and only,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.72,0:01:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,favorite little\Nbrother... moi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.68,0:01:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Awww.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.46,0:01:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Regular subtitles\Nby YayPonies\NWe have muffins!\Nhttps://yp1.yayponies.no/
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.88,0:01:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Flutter-butter!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How's the bestest\Nbig sister ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.52,0:01:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where's the love?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.40,0:01:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a little excitement\Nto see your baby brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.26,0:02:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When you left, you said mane\Ntherapy was your calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.66,0:02:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it is, sis. It is. You would\Nnot believe how much stress
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.62,0:02:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,ponies hold in\Ntheir manes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.76,0:02:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything gets limp\Nand unmanageable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No offense, but brushing alone\Nwon't solve the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.54,0:02:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What went wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.04,0:02:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing went wrong\Nper se.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.68,0:02:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just "the powers that\Nbe" were so locked into their
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.94,0:02:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"required styles"\Nand you know me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.36,0:02:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got my own style\Nand I think they were
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.76,0:02:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a little threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.64,0:02:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is lovely, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.38,0:02:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it isn't Rainbows "the\Nbest flier that ever was" Dash.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.82,0:02:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this ought be good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.34,0:02:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I shouldn't\Ntease ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.38,0:02:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the whole "super awesome\Nflyer" bit's just to impress me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.42,0:03:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, thanks for showing up for\Nmy homecoming, it's, it's sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.42,0:03:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I kinda thought there'd\Nbe more ponies here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what about your party\Nplanner friend? Sprinkle Pie?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.24,0:03:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She coulda turned this into a\Nreal house par-tay, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.40,0:03:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this place\Ncould use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.32,0:03:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Dra-ahb! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.74,0:03:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I, I ...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.06,0:03:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been meaning\Nto redecorate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.46,0:03:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, please, when I get all my\Nstuff back in here, you won't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.86,0:03:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,even remember what this\Nboring old place looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.54,0:03:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Mom, Dad? Can I talk\Nto you for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.06,0:03:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.52,0:03:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not so sure letting Zephyr\Nmove back home is a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.06,0:03:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you both\Nwant to help,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.38,0:03:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't you\Nremember last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.64,0:03:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr's just trying to\Nfind his place, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.42,0:03:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. It just seems like\Nhis place always ends up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,being your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.82,0:03:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he sort of makes\Nyou do everything for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.42,0:04:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we may not be as\Nbold as you, Fluttershy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't you worry. We know\Nhow to stand up for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.32,0:04:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were all like, "We\Nlove your free spirit, Zeph
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would be wrong to cage\Nthat. Go follow your dreams."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Zeph was just telling me\Nall about the ins and outs
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.74,0:04:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of Mane Therapy School.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.92,0:04:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all so political. I\Njust could not take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe if you stuck with\Nit for more than a few weeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, sis, but when\Nsomething's not the right fit,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.12,0:04:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this pony's gotta fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.04,0:04:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, good talk, Rainbows.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.06,0:04:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so touched you\Ncame to see me, really,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.98,0:04:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to deprive\Nyou of my presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.78,0:04:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but this Breeze needs his Zs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.42,0:04:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it's the middle\Nof the day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.36,0:04:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. SIESTA!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.70,0:04:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just gonna assume\Nyou made up my room
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.46,0:04:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I like\Nit, right, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.78,0:05:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, I almost forgot. All\Nmy stuff is out front.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.74,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna grab that for\Nme, Pops? Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.90,0:05:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Same old "Zeph."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.94,0:05:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you weren't expecting\Nto see your brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but you've been kinda\Nquiet. Even for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.60,0:05:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I am just\Nso... so peeved right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse my language.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.04,0:05:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainbow Dash! Fluttershy! It's\Nme, Pinkie Pie! Your friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.58,0:05:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, um, sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.96,0:05:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We just had lunch with\NFluttershy's parents
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll never\Nguess who showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.90,0:05:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, Mayor Mare? Cranky Doodle\NDonkey? Cheese Sandwich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.10,0:05:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Harshwhinny?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.20,0:05:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr Breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.22,0:06:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that makes more sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.50,0:06:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the look\Non your face,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.90,0:06:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm guessing it's for another\None of his 'extended' stays.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.04,0:06:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a bit peeved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.50,0:06:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr is my brother\Nand I love him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.46,0:06:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's never learned to\Ndo anything for himself
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.92,0:06:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't know why my\Nparents keep letting him
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.84,0:06:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,trot all over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.64,0:06:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if your parents won't\Nstand up for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.88,0:06:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe you need to\Nstand up for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.38,0:06:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.54,0:06:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr Breeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hey sis! Come to see me work\Nmy magic and turn this place
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.44,0:06:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,from drab to fab, huh?\NWell, watch and learn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see what\Nyou're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.86,0:06:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm getting\Nrid of this old stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.08,0:06:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so I can turn the back\Nhouse into my art studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.92,0:06:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've decided I'm going\Nto be a sculptor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about\NMom's flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.80,0:07:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gonna move them so I can\Nhave my meditation patio here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.92,0:07:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,She loves replanting\Nstuff, don't you, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And Dad's been collecting\Nhis favorite bits of cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,from the factory since\Nbefore you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.78,0:07:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The very best from\Nevery production run
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.28,0:07:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,since my first day\Non the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.58,0:07:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But why hold onto\Nthe past, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just fly in\Nand change everything
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.98,0:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and Dad have\Nbuilt here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.76,0:07:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is the only\Nplace big enough
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.56,0:07:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for my studio/meditation\Ngarden.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.24,0:07:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, unless I do it\Nin the living room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.88,0:07:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I know speaking up for yourself\Ncan be hard, believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But Zephyr will never stand on\Nhis own if he can lean on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.24,0:07:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be so\Ndramatic, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.10,0:07:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and Dad just want\Nto let me be me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do plenty on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.52,0:07:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree. Which is why\Nyou should move out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.14,0:08:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Well, I mean,\NI totally would.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.54,0:08:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that's\Nwhat Mom and Dad want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.20,0:08:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.28,0:08:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.72,0:08:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know we love you, son.\NBut your sister has a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.82,0:08:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. I mean, I really\Njust came back here to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.32,0:08:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you guys company. But\Nwhatever's best for the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.86,0:08:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I just...I just gotta\Ngrab a few essentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.46,0:08:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And you definitely have\Nsomewhere else to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.76,0:08:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! There's plenty\Nof ponies who'd love
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.68,0:08:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for a little Breeze\Nto blow their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.98,0:08:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, where's Zeph\Ngonna go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.24,0:08:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure. Oh, I hope\NI did the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding?\NOne hundred percent!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:09:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey sis, your new\Nroomie's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.54,0:09:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, maybe like\Nseventy percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.46,0:09:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Zephyr?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.10,0:09:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When Mom and Dad told you to\Nfind someplace else to live,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.68,0:09:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think\Nthey meant here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.56,0:09:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not\Ntheir house,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so by definition\Nit's someplace else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.06,0:09:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I right, Rainbows? Stop\Noogling me and help settle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.84,0:09:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what? I totally\Nforgot that I promised
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to help Pinkie Pie...\Nsprinkle... something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.58,0:09:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you had\Nplenty of places to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! You can stay here--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.52,0:09:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the best! We're\Ngonna have so much fun--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.36,0:09:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,--on one condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally. Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.34,0:09:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to get a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:10:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Crackin' the whip, huh? You\Nalways were kinda bossy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr Breeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.12,0:10:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Kidding! Get a\Njob. Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are\Nwe going so early?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.26,0:10:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no idea how bad\Nmorning sun is for your mane.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.94,0:10:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember how we talked\Nabout you getting a job?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.13,0:10:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just yesterday. And\Nit's totally on my to-do list.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.00,0:10:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't expect\Nme to find something
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.04,0:10:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,befitting my\Nawesomeness overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.92,0:10:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you might\Nsay that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.70,0:10:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.06,0:10:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,These fabrics all need\Nto be dyed those colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.28,0:10:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think you\Ncan handle that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.02,0:10:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.70,0:10:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You get started while\NFluttershy and I
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,head to the store\Nfor more supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.34,0:10:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ta-ta!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.28,0:10:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.20,0:11:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for giving\Nmy brother a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.42,0:11:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I just hope he's\Nup to the task.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.42,0:11:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh darling, dyeing fabric\Nis the simplest thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.80,0:11:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You just dip cloth\Nin a bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.00,0:11:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarity! You're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.66,0:11:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you talk to\Nanimals all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.22,0:11:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I just figured it\Nruns in the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.68,0:11:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so why not outsource\Nthis stuff, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out the animal\Ncommunication thing
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.72,0:11:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't genetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.73,0:11:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr! I asked\Nyou to do this job,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.16,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not to pawn it off on\Ninnocent woodland creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.96,0:11:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. I guess you have some\Nfeelings about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.80,0:11:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but you should know it's\Nbasically your cat's fault
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for walking by and\Ngiving me the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.44,0:11:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm actually\Nkinda into this look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.20,0:11:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I guess what I'm saying\Nis... you're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:11:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha-- Oh, uggh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.42,0:12:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr, this is\Njust unacceptable!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.88,0:12:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. I guess I know when my\Nefforts aren't appreciated!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.38,0:12:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, those are tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.34,0:12:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you noticed because\Nthey're your new job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha-?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.50,0:12:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you were taking me\Nto tea with the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.80,0:12:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I said I was going\Nto tea with the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.34,0:12:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.10,0:12:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, c'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.92,0:12:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Zephyr.\NIt'll be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.22,0:12:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need a Pegasus pony to\Nfly up and wipe each window down
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.60,0:12:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from top to bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.74,0:12:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm here to make\Nsure you do it right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.00,0:12:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, Zephyr, this\Nlooks amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, like\Nyou said, it was easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.10,0:12:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Spike?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.86,0:12:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Up here!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:12:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You were supposed to supervise,\Nnot do all the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.02,0:13:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was supervising! And\Nthen Zephyr asked me about
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.00,0:13:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,different cleaning techniques\Nand which one was best
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.18,0:13:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I could--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! I did all\Nthe work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.34,0:13:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let him fool you, ol'\NSpike is quite the taskmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.82,0:13:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.62,0:13:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to ask Spike to make\Nsure I was doing it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't do it at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guarantee there\Nwon't be any fooling around
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.28,0:13:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on the next job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.78,0:13:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Next job?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.86,0:13:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Zeph.\NYou're coming with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.84,0:13:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to come\Nup with some excuse
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.70,0:13:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to hang out with\Nme, Rainbows.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.58,0:13:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just go for a fly and\Nsee where the day takes us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.48,0:13:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, we're going to\NWonderbolts' Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.48,0:13:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am going to give you a job\Nso simple and straightforward,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.56,0:13:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,not even you can weasel\Nyour way out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.66,0:13:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.50,0:14:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to zap you with\Na storm cloud. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.84,0:14:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got it. I can already feel\Nthe electricity between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.18,0:14:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainbow\NDash is crazy, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.14,0:14:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She expects me to do stuff right\Nwhen she asks me to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.20,0:14:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just quit? Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.06,0:14:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Escaped is more like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.10,0:14:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, what was\NI supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.46,0:14:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep trying? Finish\Nsomething for once?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.46,0:14:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that way, you'd actually\Nfind something you like to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.96,0:14:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That all sounds fine for your\Nfriends, but it's just not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.18,0:14:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm sorry, Zephyr, but I\Ndon't think you can live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.36,0:14:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. I'll just go\Nlive in the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.68,0:14:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,like my foreponies before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.90,0:14:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess the only breeze this\NZephyr can count on is his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.30,0:15:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww cheer up, Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.12,0:15:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it was hard, but\Nyou did the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.18,0:15:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't let Zephyr\Npull the same stuff on you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.84,0:15:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's always\Npulled on your folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello Constance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.66,0:15:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.30,0:15:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Wigford, The Breeze needs\Nnopony. We've got food...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.32,0:15:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Shelter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.54,0:15:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just need to put\Nthe ol' kettle on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.24,0:15:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, stickie-stickie\Nmake with the sparks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.32,0:15:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! What's a pony gotta do to\Nfind a decent stick around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know he needs to learn to\Ndo things for himself, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.30,0:16:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let him\Nlive like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.56,0:16:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I don't think he'd\Nmake it through the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy! Hey! I was just, um,\Ncozying up in my sleeping bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to call it\Nan early night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.96,0:16:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Such an exhausting\Nday, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.84,0:16:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.08,0:16:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know me: siesta!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.74,0:16:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,UGH! I can't do this.\NI can't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.26,0:16:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephyr, you're\Nsmart and talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.62,0:16:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You could do anything\Nif you just tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.68,0:16:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if I give everything\NI have and still fail?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.58,0:16:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I think it's\Nbetter not to try at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.54,0:16:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But then you won't\Never do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.32,0:16:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't expect you\Ntwo to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.00,0:16:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, when have\Nyou ever failed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.40,0:17:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You've literally helped save\NEquestria, like, a dozen times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.86,0:17:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was worried that\NI'd fail every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.72,0:17:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you have to do things\Neven though you might fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.06,0:17:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But failing is the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.86,0:17:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And quitting doesn't feel\Nmuch better, does it?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.30,0:17:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the deal: You\Ncan come back with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but you have to do exactly\Nwhat I say, no exceptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.38,0:17:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I will literally do\Nanything you ask me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.12,0:17:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,if it means I don't\Nhave to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, you know what you\Nhave to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.74,0:17:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Beg for help, then quit\Nwhen I get frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.64,0:17:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just kidding. Total\Nopposite of that. Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.32,0:17:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You think he can do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.86,0:17:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Everypony has times{\i0}\N{\i1} in their lives ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.78,0:17:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ when their hearts{\i0}\N{\i1} are filled with doubt ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.56,0:17:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Frustration builds up inside ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.38,0:17:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ and it makes you{\i0}\N{\i1} want to shout ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ But if you just{\i0}\N{\i1} take that first step ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.04,0:18:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ the next one will appear ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.86,0:18:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ And you'll find you{\i0}\N{\i1} can walk, then run, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.06,0:18:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ then fly into{\i0}\N{\i1} the stratosphere ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.22,0:18:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ You've got to give{\i0}\N{\i1} it your best ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.62,0:18:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ so you can{\i0}\N{\i1} pass the test ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.70,0:18:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Give it everything{\i0}\N{\i1} that you've got ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.08,0:18:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ And we know you can win ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.38,0:18:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ You just have to begin ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.44,0:18:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Have to give it{\i0}\N{\i1} your very best shot ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.06,0:18:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ There are times when{\i0}\N{\i1} you want to give up ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.86,0:18:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ when you think that{\i0}\N{\i1} you can't go on ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.68,0:18:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ But if you fight through{\i0}\N{\i1} with all of your might ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.58,0:18:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ You will find that{\i0}\N{\i1} you can't go wrong ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ That you could do{\i0}\N{\i1} it all along! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Everypony has times{\i0}\N{\i1} in their lives ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.98,0:19:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ When their hearts{\i0}\N{\i1} are filled with doubt ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.90,0:19:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ But if you just{\i0}\N{\i1} give it your all, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.68,0:19:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ you'll start to work it out ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.52,0:19:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ And I know I can't give up too{\i0}\N{\i1}soon, get myself in the zone. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.10,0:19:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ And I find I can{\i0}\N{\i1} walk then run... ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ Then flyyyyyy ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.20,0:19:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ I can do it on my own! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.68,0:19:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ You can do it on your own! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.12,0:19:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ♪ I can do it on my own!{\i0}\N{\i1} I can do it on my own. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.28,0:19:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it. I actually finished\Nsomething. By myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.98,0:19:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks exactly\Nlike it's supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.30,0:19:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you could do\Nit, Zephyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.38,0:19:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.70,0:20:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do now. Thanks, for\Nbelieving in me, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what big\Nsisters are for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.96,0:20:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Zeph, now that you've\Naccomplished this, what's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.46,0:20:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything I want! I mean,\Nthe sky's the limit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.84,0:20:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, I've got\Nsome baby steps in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.22,0:20:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for dinner, Mr. and Mrs.\NShy. It was great, as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.52,0:20:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, dear, for\Nnot giving up on Zephyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.90,0:20:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,After all these years\Nof pining for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.30,0:20:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it must be so satisfying to\Nsee him on the right track.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.28,0:20:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard from\NZephyr? Is he doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.98,0:20:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you, he's\Na brand new pony.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.32,0:20:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So full of drive\Nand determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.50,0:20:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.60,0:20:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who graduated from\Nmane therapy training?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.50,0:20:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.98,0:21:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so handsome!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.68,0:21:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so proud of\Nyou, Zephyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.92,0:21:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only a\Nmatter of time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.48,0:21:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,before they recognized\Nmy true genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.40,0:21:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But actually doing the\Nwork probably helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.76,0:21:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wouldn't have\Nif it weren't for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.88,0:21:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh I just gave you\Nsome encouragement;
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.18,0:21:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you did this on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.24,0:21:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And honestly, right now I\Nfeel like I can do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.04,0:21:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Except find a place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.40,0:21:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can still crash here\Nfor a few days, right?
